1) The 3-Gate Check (fast mental loop)

Gate 1 — Multiplicity

“Did more than one proxy react?”

* 1 node → ignore or hold
* 2–3 nodes → investigate
* 3+ aligned → actionable

⸻

Gate 2 — Timing Coherence

“Did they react within a plausible window?”

* tight clustering → likely real signal
* scattered timing → likely noise

⸻

Gate 3 — Causal Plausibility

“Is there a physical or logical mechanism?”

* clear cause → proceed
* vague “feels like” → pause

⸻

2) Friction Test (this is the Kintsugi part)

Before locking belief:

* Try to break it
    * What would disprove this?
    * What’s an alternative explanation?

If it survives:
→ promote signal

If not:
→ discard or downgrade

⸻

3) Confidence Tiers

* Tier 0 → interesting pattern (no action)
* Tier 1 → weak signal (observe)
* Tier 2 → probable (prepare)
* Tier 3 → confirmed (act)

